description: External alterations to residential blocks A, B and E involving the construction of balconies and terraces, replacement fenestration, recladding and associated repair and refurbishment of brick work
decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.
Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).
| The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with drawing title number(s)
302-BPL(18)E01; 302-BPL(20)E01; 302-EB(20)E01 Rev F; 302-EPL(18)E01; 302-EPL(20)E01 Rev F; 302-SK(21)P01 Rev A; Planning Statement; and Design Statement 302-RT01 Rev E
Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, in the interest of proper planning.
| The materials to be used for the external surfaces of the development shall match and complement the existing building.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings, in accordance with adopted Development (or Core) Strategy (April 2012); policies 7.4, and 7B of the Development Management DPD (2013); policies 7.4 and 7.6 of the London Plan (2015); and National Planning Policy Framework (2012).
